Meniere's (say 'men-YEERS') disease is a problem of the inner ear that affects hearing and balance.
It causes sudden attacks of vertigo that make you feel like you are spinning.
It can also cause a loud ringing in the ears called tinnitus, a temporary loss of hearing, and a feeling of fullness in the ear.
Your hearing loss may not get better.
The cause of Meniere's disease is not known, but it may be related to a uid imbalance in the inner ear.
The goal of treatment is to make the vertigo less severe until the attack ends.
Some people mn prevent attacks by eating a diet low in sodium and by doing exercises to improve balance.
Surgery is an option for some people.
Follow-up care is a key part of yourtreatment and safety.
Be sure to make and go to all appointments, and call your doctor if you are having problems.
It's also a good idea to know your test results and keep a list of the medicines you take.
How can you mre for yourself at home?
During an attack of vertigo, lie down and hold your head very still until the feeling passes.
This may help you mpe with vertigo.
